  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n                        \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.yankodesign.com/images/design_news/2025/07/8bitdo-pro-3-controller-comes-with-swappable-buttons-and-cross-platform-compatibility/8BitDo-Pro-3-Controller-14.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.yankodesign.com/2025/07/17/8bitdo-pro-3-controller-comes-with-swappable-buttons-and-cross-platform-compatibility/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"8BitDo Pro 3 controller comes with swappable buttons and cross platform compatibility\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.yankodesign.com/images/design_news/2025/07/8bitdo-pro-3-controller-comes-with-swappable-buttons-and-cross-platform-compatibility/8BitDo-Pro-3-Controller-14.jpg\" data-cfsrc=\"https://www.yankodesign.com/images/design_news/2025/07/8bitdo-pro-3-controller-comes-with-swappable-buttons-and-cross-platform-compatibility/8BitDo-Pro-3-Controller-14.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e8BitDo is on a roll, launching accessories for the gaming community, and also demonstrating that the industry is on an upward graph when it comes to popularity. The gaming accessories maker is giving every kind of gamer a reason to buy their gamepads. Be it someone who loves playing old-school arcade fighting titles, someone like me who fancies racing games more than anything else, or an indie game lover who is spoilt for choices.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Pro 2 controller released in 2021 was a big hit, and now 8BitDo has released the upgraded version of the popular gamepad. Dubbed Pro 3, the gamepad visually resembles the PlayStation DualSense controller design. There are side-by-side sticks that now have drift-resistant TMR technology. This is the brand’s first-ever controller with easy swappable ABXY buttons. In a market flooded with good gaming controllers at reasonable prices